公司损失 2 亿至 3 亿美元，是埃隆马斯克削减成本的早期目标之一。据报道，谷歌“努力”与这位亿万富翁取得联系，讨论 Twitter 的未付账单，并一度试图通过 SpaceX 与他取得联系，SpaceX 也与这家科技巨头有业务往来。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/twitter-has-supposedly-started-paying-its-google-cloud-bill-again-213824844.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/twitter-has-supposedly-started-paying-its-google-cloud-bill-again-213824844.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c684b734-3fb7-4233-a0ae-bb9779b5937b</guid><dc:creator>伊戈尔博尼法西奇</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 21 Jun 2023 21:38:24 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687383506</ingested><modified> 2023-06-21T21:38:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Igor Bonifacic]]></category><media:content height="3667" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/402fb660-1079-11ee-b7ff-8057da3289d3" width="5500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3667" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/402fb660-1079-11ee-b7ff-8057da3289d3" width="5500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Gonzalo Fuentes / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Elon Musk, Chief Executive Officer of SpaceX and Tesla and owner of Twitter, gestures as he attends the Viva Technology conference dedicated to innovation and startups at the Porte de Versailles exhibition centre in Paris, France, June 16, 2023. REUTERS/Gonzalo Fuentes     TPX IMAGES OF THE DAY]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[FRANCE-TECH/MUSK]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Cellular satellite test successfully beams 4G data from space to a regular phone]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>今年早些时候，AST SpaceMobile 在 AT&amp;T 的帮助下，成功地将现成的三星 Galaxy S22 连接到近地轨道上的卫星，完成了<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/att-completes-the-first-space-based-voice-call-using-a-standard-smartphone-120012437.html">双向语音通话</a></ins>.该公告标志着基于卫星的蜂窝通信的一个重要里程碑。现在该公司表示，距离将这项技术带给消费者又近了一步。</p><p>周三，AST <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20230621154227/en/AST-SpaceMobile-Confirms-4G-Capabilities-to-Everyday-Smartphones-Directly-From-Space">分享了</a>它最近在夏威夷完成的多项测试，其工程师看到从公司的 BlueWalker 3 卫星到地面上未修改的手机的下载速度为 10Mbps。 AT&amp;T 网络负责人 Chris Sambar 表示：“在卫星到智能手机的测试中成功达到两位数的下载速度，让我们离确保全美国的人们无论身在何处都能保持联系更近了一步。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>下一步，AST 希望通过 5G 信号将手机连接到 BW3。 SpaceX 猎鹰 9 号于 9 月将原型卫星送入近地轨道。 BW3 的尺寸为 693 平方英尺，拥有迄今为止所有商业卫星中最大的天线，并且很容易成为其中之一<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.space.com/bluewalker-3-satellite-interference-worries-astronomers">夜空中最亮的物体</a></ins>，让天文学家很难<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/were-entombing-the-earth-in-an-impenetrable-shell-of-dead-satellites-163002560.html">进行他们的研究</a></ins>.</p><p> AT&amp;T 是美国少数几家希望利用卫星为服务欠缺的农村社区提供服务的运营商之一。 2021 年，威瑞森<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/verizon-amazon-project-kuiper-satellite-internet-133327300.html">与亚马逊合作</a></ins>使用公司的<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/verizon-amazon-project-kuiper-satellite-internet-133327300.html">柯伊伯计划</a></ins>用于无线访问的卫星网络。最近，T-Mobile 表示将与<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spacex-is-getting-ready-to-test-its-starlink-satellite-to-cell-phone-service-181810564.html">太空探索技术公司</a></ins>测试支持 Starlink 的设备。与 AT&amp;T 一样，该运营商表示现有电话应与其卫星产品兼容。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/cellular-satellite-test-successfully-beams-4g-data-from-space-to-a-regular-phone-200318927.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/cellular-satellite-test-successfully-beams-4g-data-from-space-to-a-regular-phone-200318927.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5e0feba5-a46c-4bab-aedf-770792b1e965</guid><dc:creator>伊戈尔博尼法西奇</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 21 Jun 2023 20:03:18 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687377801</ingested><modified> 2023-06-21T20:03:38+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Telecommunication]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Igor Bonifacic]]></category><media:content height="3029" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/18bb6cc0-106d-11ee-97c7-4f89a16a8483" width="4000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3029" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/18bb6cc0-106d-11ee-97c7-4f89a16a8483" width="4000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[AST SpaceMobile]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[AST SpaceMobile graphic showing an engineer using an un